he was Chuck Drakner.

02:29.830 --> 02:32.378
Who's Conrad Costas?
My uncle.

02:32.380 --> 02:34.280
He was a detective
in Cleveland.

02:34.290 --> 02:36.451
Honest cop
in a dirty station house,

02:36.460 --> 02:38.030
rooting out corruption.

02:38.040 --> 02:39.200
Sounds like a great story.

02:39.210 --> 02:40.416
Right?

02:40.420 --> 02:42.661
I thought, why not adapt it
for the screen?

02:42.670 --> 02:43.989
So I did.

02:44.000 --> 02:45.536
And then you sent it
to Jim Force,

02:45.540 --> 02:47.531
formally Chuck Drakner.

02:47.540 --> 02:50.077
He said it was amateur work,
at best.

02:50.080 --> 02:51.320
Mm.

02:51.330 --> 02:52.991
