12:28.880 --> 12:30.165
[ Groans ]

12:30.170 --> 12:32.821
Come on, you -- you said you
were gonna show me the ropes.

12:32.830 --> 12:35.492
Yeah, okay, you got to
get yourself a shooting script,

12:35.500 --> 12:37.491
and to do that,
you got to get on set.

12:37.500 --> 12:40.242
Okay, I'm just supposed to,
like, sneak past security?

12:40.250 --> 12:42.241
I can get you on set,
guaranteed.

12:42.250 --> 12:45.413
Thank you.
I owe you one.

12:45.420 --> 12:47.570
Alright,
I'll cash it in.

12:47.580 --> 12:48.990
Right now.

12:49.000 --> 12:50.160
What's going on
with you, Dex?

12:50.170 --> 12:52.707
You've been acting
so snealq lately.

12:52.710 --> 12:54.075
What? I'm not...

12:54.080 --> 12:55.456
I'm fine.

12:55.460 --> 12:57.280
What's up with that letter
you've been hiding from me?

13:02.500 --> 13:05.822
I think it might be
a way to find my parents.

13:12.250 --> 13:13.740
The letter is
from my Aunt Maribel,

13:13.750 --> 13:14.956
my mom's older sister.

13:14.960 --> 13:16.916
We used to be, um --
We used to be pretty close.

13:16.920 --> 13:18.376
You think she knows
where your folks are?

13:18.380 --> 13:19.916
Maybe.

13:19.920 --> 13:22.662
When I got back from Afghanistan
and I realized they were gone,

13:22.670 --> 13:25.036
Maribel was the first person
that I went to go and see.

13:25.040 --> 13:27.827
Um, but I couldn't find her,
either.
Hmm.

13:27.830 --> 13:30.993
I just assumed that Maribel
and my parents were somewhere.

13:31.000 --> 13:32.376
I don't --
I don't know where.

13:32.380 --> 13:34.075
Well, how long
you had the letter?

13:34.080 --> 13:35.536
About five years.

13:35.540 --> 13:37.201
Did you say five years?
Well, I --

13:37.210 --> 13:39.371
Life took over, okay?
And I wasn't ready.

13:39.380 --> 13:40.870
I was -- I was
furious with them

13:40.880 --> 13:42.666
and with -- with --
with her, too.
Right.

13:42.670 --> 13:43.910
I don't know.

13:43.920 --> 13:45.319
Ansel has been talking
about our folks lately,

13:45.330 --> 13:47.378
so I thought,
maybe I'll look her up.

13:47.380 --> 13:48.995
Maybe you'll look her up?
Dex...

13:49.000 --> 13:50.661
What is she gonna say?
What is she gonna say?

13:50.670 --> 13:53.241
What -- What -- What if
we were just abandoned?

13:53.250 --> 13:55.161
Well, then at least you would
have your answers, right?

13:55.170 --> 13:56.819
Right now,
you just have questions.

13:56.830 --> 13:59.287
Hey, I think
you should do it.

14:02.000 --> 14:03.536
Where the hell are we?

14:03.540 --> 14:05.417
This is Hollywood.

14:05.420 --> 14:06.705
[ Chuckling ] This is
the real Hollywood.

14:06.710 --> 14:08.416
Isn't it great?
Y-Yeah.

14:08.420 --> 14:09.876
Alright, right up here,
we're gonna go

14:09.880 --> 14:11.165
to Special Extras.

14:11.170 --> 14:13.161
They cast background
for movies.

14:13.170 --> 14:16.207
50 bucks to the receptionist
can get you on any set in town.

14:16.210 --> 14:17.871
And you know this
because?

14:17.880 --> 14:19.745
'Cause I dated an actress.
She was an extra.

14:19.750 --> 14:21.160
Okay.

14:21.170 --> 14:23.821
So -- S-So,
once I'm on set...

14:23.830 --> 14:26.321
When you're on set,
you find the script supervisor.

14:26.330 --> 14:28.286
The scripty will have
a whole production draft.

14:28.290 --> 14:29.666
What does "scripty" do?

14:29.670 --> 14:31.570
They make sure the actors say
all their lines right, I think.

14:31.580 --> 14:34.822
Okay, so I just need to --
to steal scripty's script.

14:34.830 --> 14:36.991
Yeah.
It's not that complicated.

14:37.000 --> 14:38.877
Okay.
Let's do it.

14:42.880 --> 14:44.416
Excellent, Miles.

14:44.420 --> 14:46.411
We're very pleased
to host you tomorrow night.

14:46.420 --> 14:48.285
Pre-invoice is on its way.

14:48.290 --> 14:50.326
Standard pricing,
no surprises, yes.

14:50.330 --> 14:51.911
[ Chuckles ]
I'll see you at 8:00.

14:51.920 --> 14:53.490
[ Cellphone beeps ]

14:53.500 --> 14:54.990
[ Chuckles ]
He's in, hermano!

14:55.000 --> 14:57.207
We're talking
Lambo dinero!

14:57.210 --> 14:58.529
Grey said no.

14:58.540 --> 15:00.371
Grey didn't know how much
dough he could rake in

15:00.380 --> 15:02.871
with an event for
200 thirsty party people.

15:02.880 --> 15:04.416
When he sees
how we killed it

15:04.420 --> 15:06.991
and he's swimming in cash,
he'll wish he said yes.

15:07.000 --> 15:09.321
We're just fulfilling his wish.
[ Chuckles ]

15:11.330 --> 15:14.413
I'm not breaking my rules

15:14.420 --> 15:16.706
Lieutenant, I don't know
what the hell your problem is,

15:16.710 --> 15:19.918
but ifI were a thinking man,
I'd say you were on the take!

15:19.920 --> 15:21.535
Now...

15:23.330 --> 15:24.820
Line!

15:24.830 --> 15:26.707
"Are you going to
get out of my way,

15:26.710 --> 15:27.995
or am I going to
go through you?"

15:28.000 --> 15:30.457
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
That's right.

15:32.040 --> 15:33.371
Can I take it
back a bit?

15:33.380 --> 15:35.166
[ Light powers down ]

15:35.170 --> 15:37.161
Man: We lost a light!
And that's a cut.

15:37.170 --> 15:40.037
[ Bell rings ]
Man: Ah, sorry.
Sorry, everybody.

15:44.710 --> 15:46.951
My chair doesn't have
my name on it?

15:46.960 --> 15:48.780
Everyone else's does.

15:48.790 --> 15:50.417
That's either
a stupid...

15:56.620 --> 15:58.326
Freddie: Hey!

15:58.330 --> 15:59.570
Can I borrow you?

16:02.330 --> 16:04.286
I butchered that scene.
Can you run lines with me?

16:04.290 --> 16:08.169
My stand-in is lighting.
Yeah, sure, okay.

16:08.170 --> 16:09.319
[ Clears throat ]

16:10.960 --> 16:13.326
They had women on the force
in the '505?

16:13.330 --> 16:14.706
Oh, yeah, sure.

16:14.710 --> 16:16.166
Cleveland was
very progresswe.

16:16.170 --> 16:17.990
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

16:18.000 --> 16:19.206
And for what it's worth,

16:19.210 --> 16:20.871
I thought you did a great job
with that scene.

16:20.880 --> 16:22.450
Really?
Yeah.

16:22.460 --> 16:23.449
Huh.

16:23.460 --> 16:24.700
Well, i-it'll be better,
you know?

16:24.710 --> 16:26.496
I-I'm just
working off the rust.

16:26.500 --> 16:29.492
Wait, you -- you were in
"The Long Road Home," right?

16:29.500 --> 16:32.492
_ Yeah.
Nine years ago.

16:32.500 --> 16:33.489
Wow.

16:33.500 --> 16:34.660
God,
that was a great movie.

16:34.670 --> 16:36.319
Thanks.
[ Chuckles ]

16:36.330 --> 16:38.070
What have you been up to,
um, since then?

16:38.080 --> 16:39.320
What have I been doing
since then?

16:39.330 --> 16:41.457
You really gonna ask me that?
Well, no, I -- I --

16:41.460 --> 16:42.700
Some advice -- Google
the star of the movie

16:42.710 --> 16:44.610
before you get on set.
Okay.

16:44.620 --> 16:46.497
Or scroll through
the archives of TMZ.

16:46.500 --> 16:49.116
You'll have your answer --
coke and rehab.

16:49.120 --> 16:51.031
That's what I've been doing.
Now you know.

16:51.040 --> 16:52.496
Okay.

16:52.500 --> 16:54.741
Look, I'm sorry. I didn't mean
to, uh, offend you.

16:54.750 --> 16:55.819
It just --
My brother and I,

16:55.830 --> 16:57.115
we watched
"The Road Home."

16:57.120 --> 16:58.417
It was a --
It was a good memory.

16:58.420 --> 17:00.991
So...

17:01.000 --> 17:02.285
[ Sighs ]

17:02.290 --> 17:04.781
No, I'm -- I'm sorry
I snapped at you.

17:04.790 --> 17:06.166
It's nerves.

17:06.170 --> 17:08.286
A lot of people
think I'm a joke,

17:08.290 --> 17:10.497
and this is
my chance at a comeback.

17:10.500 --> 17:14.038
I don't want my last picture
to be my mug shot.

17:14.040 --> 17:16.417
I -- I get it.

17:16.420 --> 17:19.036
Oh, okay.

17:19.040 --> 17:20.325
I'm the lieutenant,
right?

17:20.330 --> 17:21.820
Yeah. Go.
Okay.

17:21.830 --> 17:24.708
Listen, Costas, the mayor's
breathing down my neck,

17:24.710 --> 17:26.871
and I hate --
I hate his halitosis.

17:26.880 --> 17:29.826
I need you to drop this case
like a bad habit.

17:32.000 --> 17:33.206
What is it?

17:33.210 --> 17:34.666
Uh, "Lieutenant, I --"
Go again.

17:34.670 --> 17:36.114
Start -- D-Do it again.
Got it.

17:36.120 --> 17:38.452
[ Bird squawking ]

17:43.000 --> 17:44.570
[ Car approaches ]

17:44.580 --> 17:45.911
[ Engine revs ]

17:50.670 --> 17:52.160
Wow.

17:52.170 --> 17:56.539
1973 Rallye series,
Dodge Challenger.

17:56.540 --> 18:00.249
V-8, original paint,
original leather interior.

18:00.250 --> 18:02.992
Whoa.
She's mint.

18:03.000 --> 18:04.035
Yeah, dawg.

18:04.040 --> 18:05.280
How long you had her?

18:05.290 --> 18:06.496
About 10 years.

18:06.500 --> 18:08.161
Got her
off the original owner.

18:08.170 --> 18:10.786
Nice.

18:10.790 --> 18:11.950
What?

18:11.960 --> 18:14.201
[ Sighs ]

18:14.210 --> 18:16.781
Hey, did you, uh...

18:16.790 --> 18:19.281
You spill something
on the seat?

18:19.290 --> 18:20.826
No, that was there
when I got it.

18:20.830 --> 18:22.206
Only blemish, though.

18:22.210 --> 18:24.201
Dude kept it in a garage
in the Valley.

18:24.210 --> 18:26.030
Hardly ever drove it.

18:26.040 --> 18:27.746
Is that right?

18:27.750 --> 18:29.286
Kind of a crime, right?

18:29.290 --> 18:31.372
Hey,
you happen to remember

18:31.380 --> 18:33.496
the guy's name
you bought this from?

18:33.500 --> 18:36.287
Irish or something,
like...

18:36.290 --> 18:37.700
McConnell, I think.

18:42.420 --> 18:43.785
You're all
a bunch of finks!

18:43.790 --> 18:45.417
Am I the only one

18:45.420 --> 18:48.912
who will put his ass on the line
for Cleveland?!

18:48.920 --> 18:51.411
For -- For...

18:51.420 --> 18:53.490
For -- For -- For --

18:53.500 --> 18:54.535
"For justice."

18:54.540 --> 18:57.031
For justice!

18:57.040 --> 18:59.110
Son of a bitch!

18:59.120 --> 19:02.453
I'm sorry. I need --
I need five.

19:02.460 --> 19:03.745
Second assistant director:
And that's a cut.

19:03.750 --> 19:05.456
[ Bell rings ]

19:05.460 --> 19:07.872
Don't say anything.

19:07.880 --> 19:10.030
Rumor is, there's
buffalo wings at crafty.

19:10.040 --> 19:11.701
Get 'em quick.
No secrets on set.

19:11.710 --> 19:13.246
Am I right?
Thanks for the tip.

19:13.250 --> 19:15.036
Mm-hmm.

19:23.080 --> 19:26.993
Hey, there's, uh, buffalo wings
at crafty, going fast.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.912
Buffalo wings?
Hell yes.

19:39.460 --> 19:41.200
[ Knock on door ]

19:41.210 --> 19:43.326
[ Daniel Indart and Luis Eric's
"Mambo Dance" plays ]

19:43.330 --> 19:45.161
Hey, is this
Events by Tookie?

19:45.170 --> 19:47.377
Who are you?
Randy Huffernan.

19:47.380 --> 19:49.450
The kid said I could
come change back here.

19:49.460 --> 19:51.530
Change why?
Into what?

19:51.540 --> 19:53.872
Uh,
I'm the entertainment.

19:53.880 --> 19:56.747
Mambo

19:56.750 --> 20:01.665
[ Extreme's Cha Cha Un Dos"
plays ]

20:01.670 --> 20:04.821
Kenny: It's all cool.
She's gonna love it.

20:04.830 --> 20:06.821
I said,
get entertainment,

20:06.830 --> 20:09.993
like a karaoke machine
or a juggler.

20:10.000 --> 20:11.319
But a Wino-gram?

20:11.330 --> 20:13.821
From a-a dude who just might be
a legit wino?

20:13.830 --> 20:16.242
Maybe I haggled too hard.

20:16.250 --> 20:17.706
Mm.

20:17.710 --> 20:19.200
I think
they sent the "B" team.

20:19.210 --> 20:23.988
Vamos papi pa'donde el
bombillito no alumbra

20:24.000 --> 20:26.491
The entertainment
looks a little...raw.

20:26.500 --> 20:29.742
Yeah, my cousin
never fails to...fail.

20:29.750 --> 20:32.958
Laura: Took?
Hey.

20:32.960 --> 20:35.110
Canola and cayenne.
Receipt's in the bag.

20:35.120 --> 20:37.031
We_ran low.
My Wife, Laura.

20:37.040 --> 20:38.530
Nice to meet you.
Miles.

20:38.540 --> 20:39.666
You too.

20:39.670 --> 20:41.820
And it was 23 miles
round trip.

20:41.830 --> 20:43.707
50 cents a mile,
standard pricing.

20:43.710 --> 20:45.166
Alright.
Look, I gotta go, Took.

20:45.170 --> 20:47.411
Mira.
Que pasa?

20:47.420 --> 20:50.071
That's a lot of va-voom
for book club, huh?

20:50.080 --> 20:52.412
It was
the only thing clean.

20:52.420 --> 20:54.411
I'm home late, okay?

20:56.830 --> 20:58.570
Se que no quieres creer cuanto
te puedo alumbrar
[ Glass shatters ]

20:58.580 --> 21:00.207
Watch the broken glass!

21:00.210 --> 21:01.700
That's cost plus,
by the way.

21:01.710 --> 21:04.918
Look, Took, now might be a good
time to talk about that invoice.

21:04.920 --> 21:07.241
There was a $50 line item
for grenadine?

21:07.250 --> 21:08.456
Mm, standard pricing.

21:08.460 --> 21:09.996
Note quedes ahi parada

21:10.000 --> 21:13.208
Unete a mi vacilon,
note quedes ahi parada

21:13.210 --> 21:15.997
Hey, Mom, how's, uh --
how's the birthday?

21:16.000 --> 21:17.820
I'm having
a wonderful time.

21:17.830 --> 21:18.876
Yes?
Yes.

21:18.880 --> 21:20.029
Good.
We needed this, Miles.

21:20.040 --> 21:21.450
Thank you.
Good.

21:21.460 --> 21:24.497
Ladies [burps]
and gentle-germs.

21:24.500 --> 21:26.661
May I have your attentions?
Oh, my God.

21:26.670 --> 21:29.537
Mom, okay, look,
this wasn't the original plan.

21:29.540 --> 21:30.529
I...
Okay?

21:30.540 --> 21:31.996
Okay.
...would like to perform,

21:32.000 --> 21:35.072
for the birthday girl,
a special rendition...

21:35.080 --> 21:37.321
[ Chuckles ]
...of "You Light Up My Life."

21:37.330 --> 21:38.740
[ Chuckles nervously ]

21:38.750 --> 21:40.456
[ Cellphone beeps ]

21:40.460 --> 21:43.327
[ Crowd murmurs ]

21:43.330 --> 21:45.537
Oh, damn this thing.

21:45.540 --> 21:46.529
[ Cellphone beeps ]

21:46.540 --> 21:47.996
Sorry.

21:48.000 --> 21:49.456
Forget device.

21:49.460 --> 21:50.700
[ Burps ]

21:50.710 --> 21:52.450
He really is drunk,
isn't he?

21:52.460 --> 21:53.575
[ Burps]
Oh...

21:53.580 --> 21:56.117
Oh'
[ Crowd gasps ]

21:56.120 --> 21:58.497
Is it playing?

21:58.500 --> 22:00.707
Oh...
[ Hiccup ]

22:01.920 --> 22:03.319
Dex: Yeah,
you nailed it, Camille.

22:03.330 --> 22:05.958
The shooting script
is identical to yours.

22:05.960 --> 22:07.996
Force ripped you off.
I can't believe it.

22:08.000 --> 22:09.991
So, how do we
get them to comply?

22:10.000 --> 22:11.991
Well, that's
not really my department.

22:12.000 --> 22:13.740
I'm not an agent
or a lavwer.

22:13.750 --> 22:14.990
I wouldn't trust you
if you were.

22:15.000 --> 22:17.070
But they should put my name
on it, right?

22:17.080 --> 22:18.320
Uh, yeah.

22:18.330 --> 22:20.491
Yeah, and, um, from
the reading I've been doing,

22:20.500 --> 22:22.036
they should be
paying you, too.

22:22.040 --> 22:24.372
To think that I could be a paid
writer in Hollywood?

22:24.380 --> 22:26.325
You're making my dreams
come true, Dex.

22:26.330 --> 22:28.821
Uh, I'll -- I'll do my best,
Camille, okay?

22:28.830 --> 22:30.991
I'll, um, call you
ifI hear anything, okay?

22:31.000 --> 22:32.991
Bye.

22:34.290 --> 22:36.372
Hey.

22:36.380 --> 22:38.996
What you doing?
I'm packing.

22:39.000 --> 22:40.991
Why?
'Cause I'm going home.

22:41.000 --> 22:42.115
What about the car?

22:42.120 --> 22:44.281
Forget the car, okay?
I hate the car.

22:44.290 --> 22:46.827
The car sucks and LA. sucks,
and I'm going home.

22:46.830 --> 22:48.491
Because?

22:48.500 --> 22:51.162
_ Because
it's my dad's car.

22:51.170 --> 22:52.159
Mm-hmm,
you told me that.

22:52.170 --> 22:54.570
You don't understand.
It's his actual car.

22:54.580 --> 22:56.662
Like, the same vehicle.

22:56.670 --> 22:58.160
My father, a man
I haven't talked to

22:58.170 --> 23:02.163
in, I don't know, 20 years,
is here in LA,

23:02.170 --> 23:04.115
and he lives in the Valley,
okay?

23:04.120 --> 23:05.610
Your dad lives in LA?

23:05.620 --> 23:07.668
Yeah, and that's why I'm flying
back to Portland, alright?

23:07.670 --> 23:09.376
Well, no,
you're running away.

23:09.380 --> 23:10.529
You know what, Dex?

23:10.540 --> 23:12.371
I-I never should have
let you talk me into this.

23:12.380 --> 23:14.029
You're the one who told me
to come down here.

23:14.040 --> 23:16.452
I'm leaving.
[ Scoffs ]

23:16.460 --> 23:19.202
Weren't you the one telling me
that I should talk to my family?

23:19.210 --> 23:20.666
Yes, I was, and
that's very different.

23:20.670 --> 23:22.535
_How? _
Because it's your family.

23:22.540 --> 23:25.111
Grey, this is a sign.
Okay, what's the sign?

23:25.120 --> 23:26.371
You were meant to
come on this trip.

23:26.380 --> 23:28.610
W-What are the chances
of this happening?

23:28.620 --> 23:31.327
You always said that if
you ever found your dad

23:31.330 --> 23:32.911
that you would finally
get some closure.

23:32.920 --> 23:35.662
Well, this is it.
This is your chance.

23:35.670 --> 23:37.786
You cannot _
run away from this.

23:41.420 --> 23:42.910
Alright, Dex.

23:42.920 --> 23:47.163
If I go see my dad,
then you go see Maribel.

23:47.170 --> 23:49.491
When it could be so easy

23:49.500 --> 23:50.990
Fine. You first.

23:51.000 --> 23:52.285
Why do I
have to go first?

23:52.290 --> 23:54.417
'Cause I have
a deal to negotiate.

23:54.420 --> 23:55.660
Fine.

23:55.670 --> 23:57.376
Fine.

23:57.380 --> 23:59.530
You know what you want

24:06.460 --> 24:08.530
Force: Okay, you need to
understand something --

24:08.540 --> 24:09.950
without me,
this script goes nowhere.

24:09.960 --> 24:11.370
It's dead in the water.

24:11.380 --> 24:14.827
So Camille should be thanking
you for ripping her off?

24:14.830 --> 24:16.821
This is your ass, Jim.

24:16.830 --> 24:18.491
I can't produce
a script I don't own.

24:18.500 --> 24:20.286
If you want to avoid
a shutdown,

24:20.290 --> 24:23.202
um, she's gonna need two million
for the script.

24:23.210 --> 24:24.666
[ Scoffs ]
I'm not quite done.

24:24.670 --> 24:27.241
Solo writing credit,
um, ten per--

24:27.250 --> 24:29.320
ten percent of
first dollar gross --

24:29.330 --> 24:31.412
No, no, and no!
16 tickets to the premiere,

24:31.420 --> 24:34.708
private air travel,
and a limo.

24:34.710 --> 24:36.280
[ Laughs ]

24:36.290 --> 24:37.826
This is the entire budget
of the movie!

24:37.830 --> 24:40.162
Okay, well, we'll give you
24 hours to answer,

24:40.170 --> 24:41.819
or, uh, we're
gonna shut it down.

24:41.830 --> 24:45.709
No, I have 14 unsold pilots
and 26 treatments.

24:45.710 --> 24:48.247
I haven't had a meeting
in a year, okay?

24:48.250 --> 24:50.787
And I've never been this close
to something real,

24:50.790 --> 24:52.576
and you're not
taking it away from me!

24:52.580 --> 24:55.538
Take away what you stole?
[ Scoffs ]

24:55.540 --> 24:58.202
It was never yours,
Mr. Drakner.

25:02.750 --> 25:04.286
Until then, baby

25:04.290 --> 25:06.702
Are you gonna let 'em hold you
down and make you cry?

25:06.710 --> 25:07.995
Don't you know?

25:08.000 --> 25:09.820
Don't you know
things can change?

25:09.830 --> 25:11.411
Things'll go your way

25:11.420 --> 25:14.321
If you hold on

25:14.330 --> 25:15.786
For one more day

25:15.790 --> 25:23.378
Yeah, ho-o-ld o-o-o-on

25:23.380 --> 25:25.280
[ Vehicle door closes ]

25:27.170 --> 25:29.456
Don't you know
things can change?

25:29.460 --> 25:31.075
Things'll go your way

25:31.080 --> 25:35.824
If you hold on
for one more day

25:35.830 --> 25:39.038
If you hold on
[ Knock on door ]

25:40.960 --> 25:43.451
Can I help you?

25:43.460 --> 25:45.496
Yeah, maybe
I'm in the wrong place.

25:45.500 --> 25:47.821
I'm looking for a guy
named Mike McConnell?

25:47.830 --> 25:50.321
Dad, someone's here
to see you!

25:50.330 --> 25:52.116
Michael: Hey, get ready.
Okay.

25:54.540 --> 25:57.498
[ Breathing heavily ]

25:57.500 --> 25:59.957
Grey.

25:59.960 --> 26:01.871
[ Chuckles ]

26:04.210 --> 26:06.201
Something to drink?

26:06.210 --> 26:08.781
Uh, no.

26:08.790 --> 26:10.371
It's good to see you.

26:14.330 --> 26:16.742
Not what _
you were expecting?

26:18.380 --> 26:19.665
No.

26:19.670 --> 26:21.956
Honestly, I thought I'd
find you in a dump somewhere.

26:21.960 --> 26:23.916
Everything
caught up to you.

26:23.920 --> 26:26.320
Yeah, well, I guess
I outran it, didn't I?

26:26.330 --> 26:28.161
Looks that way.

26:28.170 --> 26:30.536
You hear from your mom?

26:32.040 --> 26:33.780
She, uh --
She got remarried.

26:33.790 --> 26:37.499
Uh, some guy
in a laundromat business.

26:37.500 --> 26:39.377
God help him.
[ Chuckles ]

26:41.500 --> 26:45.072
Anyway, they, uh,
live in Kansas City now, so...

26:45.080 --> 26:47.457
Everybody's moved on,
I guess.

26:47.460 --> 26:49.872
Yeah.

26:49.880 --> 26:51.370
[ Clears throat ]

26:51.380 --> 26:53.371
A beard suits you.
You look good.

26:53.380 --> 26:54.824
What -- What
have you been doing?

26:54.830 --> 26:56.616
I got a bar
up in Portland now.

26:56.620 --> 26:58.611
A bar?
Yeah.

26:58.620 --> 27:00.747
That's great.
Good for you.

27:00.750 --> 27:01.876
What's it called?

27:04.000 --> 27:05.911
It's called The Bad Alibi.
[ Chuckles ]

27:05.920 --> 27:08.320
I love that name.

27:08.330 --> 27:11.379
I, uh --
I stopped drinking.

27:11.380 --> 27:14.167
Just in time for the new family,
I guess.

27:16.460 --> 27:18.416
I'm glad you're
staying out of trouble.

27:18.420 --> 27:20.411
Well,
it hasn't been easy.

27:20.420 --> 27:22.820
I imagine
it hasn't been.

27:22.830 --> 27:24.741
[ Scoffs ]

27:24.750 --> 27:26.991
You know, everything I am,
Mike, is 'cause of you.

27:27.000 --> 27:29.207
I did everything
you taught me.

27:29.210 --> 27:31.781
And by the time I realized
that it was crap,

27:31.790 --> 27:33.326
I was in jail.

27:33.330 --> 27:35.036
Is that what you
came here to tell me?

27:35.040 --> 27:36.701
I -- I was a bad father?

27:36.710 --> 27:37.995
You don't think
I know that?

27:38.000 --> 27:40.457
Well, I never
got to say it to you.

27:40.460 --> 27:44.328
You don't think I wanted to say
how -- how sorry I was?

27:44.330 --> 27:46.707
You had a long time to do that.
You never reached out to me.

27:46.710 --> 27:48.496
You told me you never wanted
to see me again, you --

27:48.500 --> 27:50.821
It was 20 years ago.
I was a 16-year-old kid.

27:50.830 --> 27:53.207
You were the dad.
You could've fixed it.

27:53.210 --> 27:55.166
You didn't. _
I guess it's ea5ier

27:55.170 --> 27:57.377
for you just to start over,
start from scratch, huh?

27:57.380 --> 27:59.075
Darlene: [ Sighs ] Okay.

28:02.000 --> 28:06.414
Honey, Mikey,
this is Grey.

28:06.420 --> 28:07.990
Hey.

28:08.000 --> 28:10.321
This is Darlene
and Mikey Junior.

28:10.330 --> 28:11.911
Hey, Mikey.

28:11.920 --> 28:14.741
It's so nice to meet you.
Yeah.

28:14.750 --> 28:17.036
You, too.

28:17.040 --> 28:20.032
I-I don't -- I don't
want to be rude,

28:20.040 --> 28:22.782
but we're running late
to baseball practice.

28:22.790 --> 28:24.451
Good luck today, Mikey.

28:24.460 --> 28:26.075
Thanks.

28:28.170 --> 28:29.455
Bye.
Michael: Bye, honey.

28:29.460 --> 28:31.826
Bye, Dad.
Bye.

28:31.830 --> 28:33.491
[ Door closes ]

28:39.210 --> 28:41.371
Beautiful family.

28:41.380 --> 28:43.826
All these photos,
these memories,

28:43.830 --> 28:46.162
you know,
holidays and birthdays

28:46.170 --> 28:48.786
and Little League in these
perfectly framed photographs.

28:48.790 --> 28:52.749
But I'll tell you,
you don't have any of me.

28:54.210 --> 28:57.247
It's like I never existed
in your life.

28:57.250 --> 28:59.536
I just -- I-I don't have
any photos of us.

29:06.380 --> 29:07.699
Now you do.

29:15.670 --> 29:17.820
[ Sighs ]

29:17.830 --> 29:19.991
I remember this day.

29:20.000 --> 29:21.911
Yeah, I do, too, Dad.

29:21.920 --> 29:23.660
It was a good day,
wasn't it?

29:23.670 --> 29:25.035
It was a great day.
Yeah.

29:27.000 --> 29:28.877
I'm sorry, son.

29:28.880 --> 29:30.700
For everything.

29:30.710 --> 29:33.417
Yeah.

29:33.420 --> 29:34.910
Me, too.

29:37.080 --> 29:41.039
[ Door opens, closes ]

29:41.040 --> 29:43.577
[ Siren wailing ]

29:43.580 --> 29:45.491
Well,
it was touch-and-go,

29:45.500 --> 29:46.990
but we made a fortune,
young brother.

29:47.000 --> 29:49.412
Five times
normal receipts.

29:49.420 --> 29:51.069
Grey's gonna be thrilled.

29:51.080 --> 29:52.820
His gun is missing.

29:55.540 --> 29:56.996
Say what?

29:57.000 --> 29:59.412
"Pistol carried by
First Lieutenant
Jacob McConnell.

29:59.420 --> 30:02.287
Connecticut
Volunteer Infantry."

30:02.290 --> 30:03.826
You sure it was there?

30:03.830 --> 30:05.115
It's always there.

30:05.120 --> 30:06.451
Someone took it
from the party?

30:06.460 --> 30:09.497
Who'd keep something nice
just hanging in an office?

30:09.500 --> 30:11.491
Maybe we can replace it and
Grey won't know the difference.

30:11.500 --> 30:13.456
What's that?

30:15.920 --> 30:19.663
So, it belonged to
Grey's great-great-grandfather

30:19.670 --> 30:21.786
from the Civil War.

30:21.790 --> 30:24.247
And it was recently
appraised for --

30:24.250 --> 30:28.459
Dios mio --

30:28.460 --> 30:30.781
$22,000.

30:30.790 --> 30:32.166
We're dead meat.

30:32.170 --> 30:34.115
Yikes.

30:34.120 --> 30:35.610
[ Dog barks in distance ]

30:37.710 --> 30:39.325
Hey,
you glad you did it?

30:39.330 --> 30:41.491
Maybe at some point,
I will be,

30:41.500 --> 30:44.822
but right now, I just kind of
feel robbed, you know?

30:44.830 --> 30:47.822
I went there, and I --
I don't know --

30:47.830 --> 30:50.162
I thought we were just gonna
pick up where we left off.

30:50.170 --> 30:52.741
You get in a fight
or something?

30:52.750 --> 30:55.036
He's just not
the same guy anymore.

30:55.040 --> 30:56.951
Maybe you're not either.

30:56.960 --> 30:58.609
I don't know, the more
that I hate the guy,

30:58.620 --> 31:01.032
the more that I see myself
in him, you know?

31:01.040 --> 31:03.668
My dad was a quiet guy.

31:03.670 --> 31:06.571
Introspective.
I take more after my mom.

31:06.580 --> 31:08.207
You don't talk about your mom
that often.

31:08.210 --> 31:11.168
No.
She, um...

31:11.170 --> 31:13.877
She had a lot of fire
in her.

31:13.880 --> 31:15.996
You know, if anyone cut
in front of us in line

31:16.000 --> 31:17.786
or was rude to us,
they would, uh --

31:17.790 --> 31:19.997
they'd get an earful.

31:20.000 --> 31:22.321
Yeah, she was tough.

31:22.330 --> 31:25.788
But she couldn't watch
mowes

31:25.790 --> 31:28.611
or animals
who were being mistreated.

31:30.000 --> 31:31.456
Or robots.

31:31.460 --> 31:33.325
Did you say "robots"?

31:33.330 --> 31:36.709
Yeah, she -- she couldn't watch
humanoid robots

31:36.710 --> 31:39.702
getting kicked around
or -- or dismantled.

31:39.710 --> 31:41.530
Come to think of it,
neither can I.

31:41.540 --> 31:43.701
Well,
that is oddly specific.

31:43.710 --> 31:46.577
Whenever I think
about them leaving us,

31:46.580 --> 31:48.491
I just want to
smash something.

31:48.500 --> 31:50.877
People up and bail
for a million reasons.

31:50.880 --> 31:53.075
None of 'em good.

31:53.080 --> 31:54.820
[ Chuckles ]
Look at us.

31:54.830 --> 31:57.037
Livin'
the Hollywood dream.

31:57.040 --> 31:58.951
Well,
if there's an upside,

31:58.960 --> 32:01.110
I don't see how
things could get much worse.

32:02.290 --> 32:03.530
Oh, my God!

32:03.540 --> 32:04.950
What the hell?

32:04.960 --> 32:05.870
[ Fire alarm beeping ]

32:05.880 --> 32:07.609
Hey, Dex, you're
making it worse!

32:07.620 --> 32:09.827
Do something!
[ Grunting ]

32:09.830 --> 32:11.957
Not that!

32:11.960 --> 32:13.996
Here, put this over your mouth,
breathe through it.

32:14.000 --> 32:15.206
Let's go, let's go!

32:15.210 --> 32:16.871
[ Coughing ]

32:20.790 --> 32:23.372
Dex: Just give me a call
if you hear anything.

32:23.380 --> 32:27.999
Well, I gave them Jim Force, and
the producer, Jared Mendleton.

32:28.000 --> 32:29.115
They're gonna
look into it.

32:29.120 --> 32:31.031
Hey, that's it
for me and LA.

32:31.040 --> 32:33.167
Let's just get in the car
and go home.

32:33.170 --> 32:34.785
I can't.

32:34.790 --> 32:36.826
I came_ here
to get Camille a deal,

32:36.830 --> 32:38.878
and I'm not gonna let
a little heat scare me away.

32:38.880 --> 32:41.451
A little heat?
It was a fire bomb.

32:41.460 --> 32:45.328
Look, I think I have a way that
we could flush out the suspects.

32:45.330 --> 32:46.911
"We"?
Yeah.

32:46.920 --> 32:48.615
They're -- They're gonna
recognize me, so...

32:53.250 --> 32:55.286
Excuse me.
You know where Stage 7 is?

32:55.290 --> 32:57.246
Right around the corner.
Thanks.

32:59.080 --> 33:01.071
So, this scumbag P.I.,

33:01.080 --> 33:03.457
the one who stole
a scripty's production draft,

33:03.460 --> 33:06.611
had a Molotov cocktail tossed
in her apartment last night.

33:06.620 --> 33:08.997
You know, my friend,
who's LAPD,

33:09.000 --> 33:12.822
says that the RI. has video
of the bomber running away,

33:12.830 --> 33:15.242
but she won't turn it over
to the cops unless they pay.

33:15.250 --> 33:16.456
Can you believe it?

33:16.460 --> 33:18.826
The P.I. has a regular table
at The Roosevelt.

33:18.830 --> 33:21.537
By 5:00 pm. every day,
she's drinking martinis.

33:21.540 --> 33:23.531
So the cops are going to
broker a deal.

33:23.540 --> 33:24.666
I'm sorry. What's that?

33:24.670 --> 33:26.991
Oh, cops in the '505
didn't have beards.

33:27.000 --> 33:28.410
Are you gonna shave my beard?
Yeah.

33:28.420 --> 33:30.536
Oh, no, no, no, no.
I-I can't work like this.

33:30.540 --> 33:32.576
I quit. Thank you.

33:32.580 --> 33:35.162
So, you're saying
it's a musket?

33:35.170 --> 33:37.161
Black powder pistol.

33:37.170 --> 33:38.990
And you think someone
in my family stole it?

33:39.000 --> 33:41.116
Well, i-initially, I thought
it was the Wino-gram,

33:41.120 --> 33:42.326
who changed clothes
in there,

33:42.330 --> 33:43.820
but then Ansel said
there were a lot of folks

33:43.830 --> 33:44.876
in and out of the office
all night.

33:44.880 --> 33:46.370
Okay, Tookie,
I am trying

33:46.380 --> 33:49.247
_ to_heal a_wound _
in my immediate family.

33:49.250 --> 33:51.206
Accusing extended family
of theft?

33:51.210 --> 33:52.609
You see, that opens
a whole other wound.

33:52.620 --> 33:54.918
Look, Miles, I --
Detective Hoffman.

33:56.620 --> 33:58.781
I don't want to place blame
on anyone, believe me.

33:58.790 --> 34:01.497
But the gun is missing,
so I need your help.

34:03.170 --> 34:04.876
I'll look into it.

34:12.500 --> 34:13.956
[ Soft music plays ]

34:13.960 --> 34:16.611
Grey: You're having a martini
on a sting?

34:16.620 --> 34:18.167
Thank you.

34:18.170 --> 34:20.741
Every guidebook recommends
a martini from The Roosevelt.

34:20.750 --> 34:22.320
I'm having one.

34:22.330 --> 34:24.457
Mmm!

34:24.460 --> 34:27.167
Do yourself a favor --
dirty up with some olives.

34:27.170 --> 34:28.569
Hey, heads up.

34:28.580 --> 34:30.241
Someone's coming your way.

34:30.250 --> 34:32.377
It's Conrad Costas.

34:34.420 --> 34:36.320
You?

34:36.330 --> 34:37.877
You were the P.I.
on set?

34:37.880 --> 34:41.327
You threw a Molotov cocktail
through my Window last night?

34:46.960 --> 34:48.496
Do you have that
surveillance footage or not?

34:48.500 --> 34:51.037
[ Scoffs ] I'm not here
to answer your questions.

34:53.330 --> 34:55.537
Come on, you got to
be kidding me.

34:55.540 --> 34:56.825
Do I look like
I'm kidding?

34:56.830 --> 34:58.457
I'll shoot if you don't
hand it over right now.

34:58.460 --> 35:00.166
Dispatcher: 911.
What's your emergency?

35:00.170 --> 35:01.410
Freddie,
you're not a killer.

35:01.420 --> 35:03.957
Sorry,
but I need this part.

35:03.960 --> 35:06.702
This is a long way to go
to keep production rolling.

35:06.710 --> 35:09.531
You think I have a choice?
This was my last shot.

35:09.540 --> 35:10.871
I know.
I know how you feel.

35:10.880 --> 35:12.279
No, you don't.

35:12.290 --> 35:15.612
You don't know what it's like
to be loved like that...

35:17.540 --> 35:18.950
...and then to be forgotten

35:18.960 --> 35:20.700
like -- like --_ like
you never eXIsted.

35:23.330 --> 35:24.991
You're right. I don't.

35:25.000 --> 35:28.538
I don't, but, um,
that must hurt.

35:32.880 --> 35:34.780
I just want to
look people in the eye

35:34.790 --> 35:38.282
and -- and for them
to -- to see me.

35:40.380 --> 35:42.109
I understand.

35:46.830 --> 35:48.707
I can -- _
I can salvage this.

35:48.710 --> 35:51.031
Freddie, you can't.

35:53.670 --> 35:55.456
I'm sorry.

35:55.460 --> 35:58.167
Why don't you
hand that to me?

35:58.170 --> 36:00.491
It's just a prop.

36:00.500 --> 36:03.617
Yeah, well, I'm not gonna
tell them about it, okay?

36:07.540 --> 36:08.700
[ Sighs ]

36:12.080 --> 36:14.162
[ Police radio chatter ]

36:14.170 --> 36:15.535
I feel bad for the guy.

36:15.540 --> 36:17.872
He just didn't
want to be forgotten.

36:17.880 --> 36:19.074
Who does?

36:21.170 --> 36:23.912
Amigo! Que pasa?
Grey: I'm fine. What's up?

36:23.920 --> 36:25.319
[ Chuckles ]
That's great.

36:25.330 --> 36:28.879
So, the pistola's gone,
and maybe it was the wino,

36:28.880 --> 36:31.075
but people were
in and out of here, too.

36:31.080 --> 36:32.570
Okay, what pistola?

36:32.580 --> 36:34.207
The Civil War gun
in your office.

36:34.210 --> 36:35.575
I put it in a safe
in my loft.

36:35.580 --> 36:36.820
I knew you were gonna
have a party,

36:36.830 --> 36:38.240
and I didn't want it stolen.

36:38.250 --> 36:39.956
And what are you talking
about a wino?

36:39.960 --> 36:42.576
Nothing.
It's all good.

36:42.580 --> 36:44.707
Alright, we're gonna talk
about this when I get home.

36:44.710 --> 36:46.496
Si, jefe.

36:46.500 --> 36:48.411
[ Cellphone beeps ]

36:50.790 --> 36:53.167
[ Chuckles ]

36:53.170 --> 36:55.570
That's crazy.

36:55.580 --> 36:57.286
Dex: I think that
we're almost there.

36:57.290 --> 36:58.609
We've got
sole writing credit,

36:58.620 --> 37:01.828
50 grand for the script, 6
tickets to the premiere, right?

37:01.830 --> 37:03.411
Premier_e?_ _
The star's in jail.

37:03.420 --> 37:05.160
Oh, no, it's already
been recast.

37:05.170 --> 37:07.377
Yeah, he wasn't really our
first choice to begin with.

37:07.380 --> 37:10.076
Wow. Out with one,
in with another.

37:10.080 --> 37:12.878
Uh, last thing --
the title, "At All Costs."

37:12.880 --> 37:14.700
My client would like
to have that reinstated.

37:14.710 --> 37:17.326
Ooh, uh, there is
a lot of paper out there

37:17.330 --> 37:18.536
with the other title.

37:18.540 --> 37:20.531
Yeah, I think we can
come up with a compromise.

37:20.540 --> 37:21.700
Yeah?
Yeah.

37:21.710 --> 37:24.031
Alright, we have a deal.
Thank you, gentlemen.

37:24.040 --> 37:25.667
Thank you.
Mm-hmm.

37:27.500 --> 37:29.536
Hmm. I think
I have this town figured out.

37:29.540 --> 37:31.701
It's slick, it's sleazy,
but it's fun.

37:31.710 --> 37:33.166
You fit right in.
[ Chuckles ]

37:33.170 --> 37:34.706
Okay, I think
my work here is done.

37:34.710 --> 37:37.031
You ready to go home?
Not quite.

37:37.040 --> 37:39.031
No?

37:43.580 --> 37:45.241
[ Window squeaking ]

37:45.250 --> 37:47.161
Grey: Alright,
this is the place.

37:47.170 --> 37:48.910
Mm-hmm.

37:48.920 --> 37:50.535
Want me to go in
with you?

37:50.540 --> 37:52.326
[ Engine idling ]

37:52.330 --> 37:53.661
No, I'm good.

37:53.670 --> 37:55.410
Alright. I'll be here.

37:55.420 --> 37:56.910
Thanks.

38:12.120 --> 38:13.701
[ Sighs ]

38:13.710 --> 38:15.280
Could I help you?

38:15.290 --> 38:16.575
Maribel?

38:16.580 --> 38:18.571
[ Gasps ]
Hi.

38:18.580 --> 38:20.707
Oh, I don't believe it.
Um...

38:20.710 --> 38:24.498
Ooh, it's been so long!
[ Chuckles ]

38:24.500 --> 38:25.990
Look at you!

38:26.000 --> 38:27.615
[ Laughs ]
Hi.

38:27.620 --> 38:29.747
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, dear.

38:29.750 --> 38:32.116
Oh, my.

38:32.120 --> 38:35.374
Oh,
how beautiful you are.

38:35.380 --> 38:36.529
Ohh!

38:36.540 --> 38:38.610
Sit, sit, sit.
Thank you, um...

38:38.620 --> 38:39.951
[ Sighs ]

38:39.960 --> 38:41.279
Oh_...
Hi.

38:41.290 --> 38:42.325
[ Both chuckle ]

38:42.330 --> 38:43.490
You should've called.

38:43.500 --> 38:45.036
I know, I know.
I'm sorry.

38:45.040 --> 38:46.530
Oh, I'm just
so glad to see you.

38:46.540 --> 38:48.496
So happy to see you.
[ Chuckles ]

38:48.500 --> 38:50.115
It's good to see you,
too.

38:50.120 --> 38:52.827
My goodness,
you don't look a day older.

38:52.830 --> 38:54.240
[ Both chuckle ]

38:54.250 --> 38:56.115
I'm so glad
you came to visit.

38:56.120 --> 38:59.283
Yeah, me, too.
Um...

38:59.290 --> 39:02.999
Actually, I'm -- I'm
looking for Mom and Dad.

39:03.000 --> 39:06.709
I was hoping you could -- you
could tell me where they are.

39:06.710 --> 39:10.077
Sweetie. . .

39:10.080 --> 39:11.536
they passed.

39:13.580 --> 39:17.289
Mom, uh,
in the winter of '83,

39:17.290 --> 39:20.282
and -- and Dad
went the year after.

39:20.290 --> 39:22.110
Don't you remember?

39:22.120 --> 39:23.872
Um...

39:23.880 --> 39:25.416
Sorry --

39:25.420 --> 39:28.412
Tell me, how is Dex?

39:28.420 --> 39:30.570
Oh...

39:30.580 --> 39:32.821
I hope
she's safe over there.

39:32.830 --> 39:34.616
She's fine.

39:34.620 --> 39:36.872
Ah, thank goodness.

39:36.880 --> 39:39.826
Oh, she's gonna be
cross with you,

39:39.830 --> 39:42.492
leaving Ansel
in that home.

39:42.500 --> 39:44.070
I told you
it wasn't right.

39:44.080 --> 39:46.958
But when do you ever
listen to your big sister?

39:46.960 --> 39:48.530
[ Chuckles ]
Hmm?

39:48.540 --> 39:50.917
Uh...

39:50.920 --> 39:54.879
Maribel, you, um...

39:54.880 --> 39:57.451
Do you remember the last
time that -- that we spoke?

39:58.960 --> 40:02.032
The night you left.
You and David.

40:02.040 --> 40:03.951
Do -- Do you remember
where we went?

40:03.960 --> 40:05.916
You said it would be better
if I didn't know.

40:05.920 --> 40:08.662
You -- You said...

40:08.670 --> 40:11.241
you had to go leave
and you couldn't come back.

40:11.250 --> 40:13.115
Why?
[ Chuckles ]

40:13.120 --> 40:14.781
Only you know that.

40:14.790 --> 40:16.667
[ Chuckles ]

40:16.670 --> 40:18.661
Yeah, you're right.

40:20.710 --> 40:22.325
[ Sighs ]

40:22.330 --> 40:24.662
I'm so sorry, sweet girl.

40:24.670 --> 40:27.116
[ Sighs ]

40:28.460 --> 40:30.530
Are you gonna leave now?

40:32.210 --> 40:34.030
Why don't we just
sit for a while?

40:34.040 --> 40:35.826
I'd like that.

40:35.830 --> 40:37.661
[ Chuckles ]

40:37.670 --> 40:43.666
[ Band of Horses' "Funeral"
plays ]

40:54.040 --> 40:56.998
They came to a compromise
on the title --

40:57.000 --> 41:00.163
[Chuckling] "At All Costs:
The Conrad Costas Chronicles."

41:00.170 --> 41:01.740
That's worse than before.
It's un-sayable.

41:01.750 --> 41:03.661
[ Chuckles ]
Camille agreed to it.

41:03.670 --> 41:05.661
Aw, who knows?
Maybe it'll be a big hit.

41:05.670 --> 41:06.819
Mm.

41:06.830 --> 41:08.821
I'm coming up
only to show you wrong

41:08.830 --> 41:13.119
At least someone got something
out of this trip.

41:13.120 --> 41:14.917
You know, actually,
I was thinking about it.

41:14.920 --> 41:16.706
I've, uh...

41:16.710 --> 41:20.168
I spent my whole life
afraid of becoming my father.

41:20.170 --> 41:24.869
And it turns out, the guy
has got it all figured out.

41:24.880 --> 41:27.201
So, if you
do the math on it,

41:27.210 --> 41:29.701
that means I'm not destined
to be a total loser.

41:29.710 --> 41:31.246
Hmm.

41:31.250 --> 41:34.208
I'm happy you, um --
you found an answer.

41:34.210 --> 41:35.746
So did you.

41:35.750 --> 41:38.207
How so?

41:38.210 --> 41:40.667
You're brave enough
to look for your parents.

41:40.670 --> 41:42.877
You didn't know that
before.

41:47.380 --> 41:49.826
Still would've been nice,
wouldn't it?

41:49.830 --> 41:52.037
The Hollywood ending.

41:52.040 --> 41:54.497
Oh, come on.
There's no such thing.

41:57.330 --> 42:01.824
Really too late to call, so

42:01.830 --> 42:04.913
We wait for

42:07.040 --> 42:10.419
Morning to wake you,
that's all...
